frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Hidden_object to become perceptually inaccessible to potential perceivers by placing it in a Hiding_place or putting in place an Obstruction that screens the object.
In this frame, an Agent places the Theme in the Medium for an extended period of time, with the intent that the Theme will be affected by and absorb some of the Medium. '
An Obstruction blocks an Eclipsed entity partially or completely from view.
These are words describing situations in which a Perpetrator takes Goods from a  Victim or a Source.
An individual or organization, the Front, serves as a cover for an Illicit_activity or an Illicit_organization.
frameExamples: Therefore, as I passed the school, I <t>hid</t> the gun and holster in the mailbox
Ellen <t>soaked</t> the beans in the water for 30 seconds.
A small green bulb <t>concealed</t> behind the panel flashed on momentarily .
I can't believe he <t>pickpocketed</t> my gold watch !
The laundromat is a <t>front</t> for the Yakuza.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Hidden_object</fen> is the entity which is blocked from view.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who causes the Hidden_entity to be not perceptually accessible to potential perceivers.
The location in which the <fen>Hidden_object</fen> is placed so as not to be perceptually accessible.
<fen>Time</fen> denotes the interval of time during which the <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Hidden_object</fen> to become hidden from perceptual access.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the spatial setting in which the hiding event takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person performing the soaking.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the entity that changes location.
<fen>Medium</fen> is the substance in which the <fen>Theme</fen> is submerged.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> soaks the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the submerging occurs.
The entity which blocks the <fen>Eclipsed</fen> entity from view.
The entity which is blocked from view.
<fen>Perpetrator</fen> is the person (or other agent) that takes the goods away.
<fen>Victim</fen> is the person (or other sentient being or group) that owns the goods before they are taken away by the perpetrator.
<fen>Goods</fen> is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be taken away.
<fen>Source</fen> is the initial location of the goods, before they change location.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the theft occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the theft occurs.
The <fen>Front</fen> acts as a legitimate individual, organization, or enterprise, but is truly a cover for an illicit organization or activity.
The existence and activities of the <fen>Illicit_organization</fen> are concealed by the <fen>Front</fen>.
The <fen>Illicit_activity</fen> of the <fen>Illicit_organization</fen> is concealed by (the activities of) the <fen>Front</fen> .
The time at which the deceptive activity occurs
The place where the fronting occurs.
listRoleExamples:
Michael Jackson gave wine to the 13-year-old cancer patient at the center of
the molestation charges he's battling but concealed <fex>it</fex> inside a Coke can.
<fex>The deputy</fex> concealed the bayonet under his coat.
He had concealed the necklace <fex>behind him</fex>.
Ellen soaked <fex>the beans</fex> in the water for 30 seconds .
Bobby soaked the potatoes <fex>in water</fex> overnight.
The mists obscured <fex>the top of the tower</fex>.
Leslie stole the watch <fex>from the table</fex>.
Leslie STOLE the watch from Kim <fex>at dusk</fex>.
Leslie STOLE the watch from Kim <fex>in the park</fex>.
